docs.text: veteran actor clint eastwood has never looked as grizzled as he does in true crime , his latest directorial effort .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when steve everett ( his newest character ) gets angry at someone , he glares them down with those famous dirty harry eyes , furrows his brow and frowns like a grizzly bear who's just lost his cubs .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: eastwood has played some particularly despicable characters in his time , but everett could just take the cake .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he gets my vote , at least , partly because `ev' is a drunken affair-a-week womanizer who has many relationship problems , very few of which are with his wife ( diane venora ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when his colleague at the oakland tribune is in an ugly car wreck and dies , everett must take over for her at a vital interview session .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the interview is with frank beacham ( isaiah washington ) , a death-row inmate set to die at midnight for the murder of a pregnant convenience store clerk .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: eastwood furrows his brow .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as everett gradually finds information , he realizes that beacham could very well be innocent .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he interviews a key witness ( michael jeter ) , who claims that he burst in the door at pocum's foods because his car had overheated , only to see beacham standing over the dead woman's body , blood on his suspenders , gun in hand .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but everett protests : how could he have seen the gun , which was lowered by his side , with the potato chip rack in front of him ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jeter doesn't know what he's talking about .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: eastwood furrows his brow .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: crinkled expressions and all , clint is the centre of energy of true crime .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the film is by no means a standard action/suspense yarn , but a thoughtful human story in which the characters come before the shoot-outs .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: isaiah washington has a break-out performance as frank beacham , and scenes with him and his weary wife ( lisa gay hamilton ) are truly heartfelt moments .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but the best scenes are ones that feature eastwood duking it out with those in authority over him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: denis leary , as everett's editor and boss , has more than a few memorable moments of restrained anger ( you see , ev is sleeping with his wife ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but hands down , the most enjoyable segments of the film are when james woods is on camera .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: playing the big boss alan mann , woods and eastwood create amusing chemistry and laugh-out-loud punchlines .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when true crime opts for a high-speed chase to the governer's house at the finale , the quality of film-making takes an abrupt nosedive .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: eastwood was so successful with colorful character portraits that he didn't need to switch lanes .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: true crime is a tension-building , intriguing drama showcase for the talented director and star .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this is a road block he could have easily dismissed ( i furrow my brow ) .
